name: sfchronicle
text: Alameda County sees more than a half-million voters already: 6,800 walk-in voters cast their ballots on Halloween; Sunday was expected to match that. The weekend voters added to an average of 30,000 mail-in ballots posted or dropped off at vote centers. https://t.co/7vN5pCE3l3
